question: 旅券
sourceMnemonic: Your <kanji>trip</kanji> <kanji>ticket</kanji> is the ticket that lets you go on ALL of your trips. It's not your airplane ticket, it's not your boat ticket, it's the trip ticket. It's your <vocabulary>passport</vocabulary>, which allows you to take trips.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
